{"word":"φαιδρός","slug":"φαιδρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φαιδρός</b></el> <el>(φαιδρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φάω'><el>φάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>bright, beaming</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <i>sparkling</i>, of water, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>beaming with joy, bright, joyous, jocund</i>, <b>Solon.</b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-δρῶς</el>, <i>joyously, cheerily</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>φαιδρά</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}